        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 1:52PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 151 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Waugh Mountain, or 53 miles southwest of Colorado Springs, moving
south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Locally heavy rain and wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Heavy rain could cause streams to rise quickly across
central Fremont county.

Locations impacted include...
Waugh Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
